      "rationale": "Output comparison performed using mean NIH prediction error (12.3%) and RH index across five operating points. Point-by-point comparison tables provided. Experimental measurement uncertainty reported from published dataset (±8% NIH). However, the comparison relies on point estimates without formal combined uncertainty propagation; a full GUM-compliant uncertainty budget combining experimental and numerical sources was not assembled. The assessment team judged the available comparison sufficient given that four of five operating points satisfy RH < 1 and the mean error is within engineering tolerance. The overall credibility evidence package, including the mesh convergence study and turbulence model sensitivity, supports the Medium assurance declaration."
